<h1 id="using-trusts">Using Trusts</h1>

<p>Remember, In the United States, Trusts are technically their own legal entity. As such a Trust named John Smith would be distinct from an individual named John Smith. Sounds weird right? 
So with this new information we can do some interesting things now. If one had enough free time and money to set up 5 Trusts with themselves as the Trustee…</p>

<ul>
  <li>John Smith Trust 1</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 2</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 3</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 4</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 5</li>
</ul>

<p>And enough patience and willpower to use the TreasuryDirect website…</p>

<p>You’d now be able to buy upto $50,000 in Series I Savings Bond using 5 separate TreasuryDirect entity accounts.</p>

